  .col-xs-12.col-md-10.offset-md-1.offset-lg-0.col-lg-6
    %h5 The Approach
    %p
      Within this program we would focus on a number of ideas that we want to explore with The Puzzle School:
    %ul.no_shift.spaced_out
      %li
        Having students test resources and provide feedback
        in order to find the best resources students can use to learn at their own pace.
      %li
        Having students engage in hands-on group projects to suppot a healthy social environment
        and explore diverse design exercises.
      %li
        Running retrospectives at the end of each sessions to get feedback from students around what worked and didn't that
        week.
      %li
        Supporting students toward independent and small group projects they design themselves
        and will continue working on at home.

    %p
      Some of the resources and activities we've had success with include:
    %ul.no_shift.spaced_out
      %li= link_to('CodeCombat', 'https://codecombat.com/', target: '_blank')
      %li= link_to('Project Euler', 'https://projecteuler.net/', target: '_blank')
      %li= link_to('Drawing In Code', 'https://jaredcosulich.github.io/drawing_code', target: '_blank')
      %li= link_to('Marshmallow Towers', 'http://www.tomwujec.com/design-projects/marshmallow-challenge/', target: '_blank')
      %li= link_to('Tongue Depressor Bridges', 'http://courses.washington.edu/engr100/Section_Brad/01_hnd_BridgeIntro.htm', target: '_blank')

    %p
      We also developed a number of discrete challenge-based activities, including a scavenger hunt focused on
      decrypting messages using algorithms.

